ispossession of Californio rancheros to the ethnic segmentation of the firm's massive labor force. The book also covers such topics as land acquisition and reclamation, water politics, San Francisco's unique business environment, and the city's relation to its surrounding hinterlands. Above all, Igler highlights essential issues that resonate for us today: who holds the right and who has the power to engineer the landscape for market production?  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Mai 2022) 0aAnimal industryxHistoryxWest (U.S.). 0aAnimal industryzWest (U.S.)xHistory. 0aBig businessxHistoryxWest (U.S.). 0aBig businesszWest (U.S.)xHistory. 0aCattle tradexHistoryxWest (U.S.). 0aCattle tradezWest (U.S.)xHistory. 0aIndustrializationxHistoryxWest (U.S.)xUnited States, West. 0aIndustrializationzWest (U.S.)xHistory. 0aLand usexHistoryxWest (U.S.). 0aLand usezWest (U.S.)xHistory. 0aPacking-housesxHistoryxWest (U.S.). 0aPacking-houseszWest (U.S.)xHistory. 0aWater rightsxHistoryxWest (U.S.). 0aWater rightszWest (U.S.)xHistory. 7aHISTORY / United States / State & Local / West (AK, CA, CO, HI, ID, MT, NV, UT, WY).2bisacsh  aagriculture.  aamerican west.  abeef markets.  abusiness.  abutchers.  acalifornia.  aeconomics.  aenvironment.  aethnicity.  afrontier.  ahistory.  aimmigrants.  aimmigration.  aindustrial enterprises.  aindustrialism.  alabor.  aland acquisition.  aland reclamation.  aland rights.  alandscapes.  ameatpacking.  amiller and lux.  amonopoly.  anatural resources.  anature.  anonfiction.  arags to riches.  arancheros.  asan francisco.  asegregation.  awater politics.  awater rights.  awaterscapes.  awestern industrialism.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of California Press Backlis